# Environment Configuration for Playwright Test Framework
# Copy this file to .env and customize as needed for local development

# =============================================================================
# UI Testing Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Base URL for web UI testing (SauceDemo application)
# Default: https://www.saucedemo.com
# UI_BASE_URL=https://www.saucedemo.com

# =============================================================================
# API Testing Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Base URL for API testing (Restful-Booker API)
# Default: https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com
# API_BASE_URL=https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com

# API Authentication Credentials
# Used for creating/updating/deleting bookings in Restful-Booker API
# Default username: admin
# Default password: password123
# BOOKER_USER=admin
# BOOKER_PASS=password123

# =============================================================================
# CI/CD Configuration
# =============================================================================
# CI environment flag (automatically set by GitHub Actions and most CI systems)
# Set to 'true' or '1' to enable CI-specific behavior:
# - Test retries enabled (2 retries)
# - Sequential test execution (workers=1)
# - Additional JUnit XML reporting
# CI=false

# =============================================================================
# Usage Instructions
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Uncomment and modify any values you need to override
# 3. The .env file is gitignored and will not be committed
# 4. All values shown are defaults - no .env file is required for basic usage
#
# For staging/production environments, consider using Playwright projects instead:
# See playwright.config.ts for multi-environment configuration patterns
